    {
      "data_family": "leveling",
      "entries": [
        {
          "entities": [],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [],
          "text": "Your leveling experience as a Warrior in Outland will be much easier if you have acquired a strong gear set in Vanilla. If you don't already own endgame raid gear, make sure to take advantage of the heavily discounted PvP gear during pre-patch for strong catch-up items that will make your leveling in Outland much smoother."
        },
        {
          "entities": [],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [],
          "text": "Try to fight enemies at a lower level than you as much as possible to increase your chances of performing critical strikes and reduce incoming damage. This will both increase your rage generation and damage output for a more fun experience, while also speeding up your kill times and reducing your downtimes."
        },
        {
          "entities": [
            {
              "id": 25236,
              "name": "",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=25236"
            }
          ],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=25236",
              "text": ""
            }
          ],
          "text": "While it may be tempting to press that button as soon as it lights up, it is usually better to save your pooled rage for your next battle if you can simply kill your current target with another auto attack or less expensive ability."
        },
        {
          "entities": [
            {
              "id": 25225,
              "name": "",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=25225"
            }
          ],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=25225",
              "text": ""
            }
          ],
          "text": "In group content, do not underestimate the party-wide damage increase of if there are a couple Physical DPS in the group. While it may be an ungrateful job that won't reward you on the damage meter, putting good Sunders for the benefit of the group is the mark of a great Warrior, and it will be noticed."
        },
        {
          "entities": [],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [],
          "text": "As a Warrior, don't forget you can also tank dungeons regardless of your talent specialization. You will have a much easier time getting into groups for any dungeon if you agree to tank occasionally."
        },
        {
          "entities": [],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [],
          "text": "Warrior lacks self-healing and sustain, so expect a lot of downtimes during your leveling journey. Always carry appropriate level food and bandages to restore your health when needed and minimize downtimes as much as possible."
        }
      ],
      "heading": "Leveling Tips for Arms Warrior DPS in TBC Classic"
    }
  ],
